=== Noun ===
'''Taekwondo''' ''or'' '''Tae Kwon Do''' ('''태권도''')

====Etymology====
'''Tae''' means "to kick or destroy with the foot". '''Kwon''' means "to punch with the fist".  '''Do''' means "way" or "art." Hence, '''Taekwondo''' is loosely translated as "the art of kicking and punching."

====Meaning====
#a [[martial arts]] form which originated in [[Korea]] in 1955 as a unification of several forms, it is now the Korean national sport.

